WEBVTT

00:03.138 --> 00:05.020
Welcome to the Life Church Podcast.

00:06.442 --> 00:11.589
We are in Acts 2.42 community, a family on a mission to bring a life of Jesus to warranty.

00:13.131 --> 00:21.060
We hope you are ready to hear what God has to say to you today through His Word and by His Spirit.

00:21.080 --> 00:21.661
Good morning.

00:21.681 --> 00:28.690
Yes, as Lucas has said, we are continuing our series on the Raymond Road.

00:28.994 --> 00:33.100
And the headline for me this morning is confess and believe.

00:34.162 --> 00:38.189
So, Dale started a series looking at the fact that we are all sinners.

00:38.289 --> 00:40.672
We all fall short of the glory of God.

00:41.554 --> 00:44.599
Then Rob talked about how Christ died for us.

00:44.719 --> 00:54.294
Despite the fact that we were still sinners, Jesus came and became our Savior, became our bridge to God.

00:55.055 --> 00:56.818
So this week we are looking at

00:56.930 --> 01:01.756
How the process of salvation, but more what it should then cause us to do.

01:01.876 --> 01:06.982
What that revelation in Christ and following him causes us to do.

01:07.022 --> 01:10.066
And we are in Romans 10.

01:10.086 --> 01:13.810
So if you have a Bible, feel free to turn to that now.

01:13.850 --> 01:19.457
But we're looking at a specific verse, Romans 10, verse nine.

01:19.998 --> 01:26.706
And I just wanted to give a bit of context of the entire chapter before honing in on that verse.

01:26.946 --> 01:30.652
So Paul is talking to the Roman church.

01:30.712 --> 01:36.481
He is himself a Jew who has experienced conversion to Christ.

01:37.262 --> 01:46.156
And one of his main jobs, one of his main kind of callings on his life is to see people from the Jewish faith come to faith in Jesus.

01:47.318 --> 01:52.466
And so a lot of this chapter is trying to explain how, you know, we have maybe

01:52.642 --> 01:58.552
been trying to earn our salvation by doing things, by sticking to the law, by having all these rules.

01:58.993 --> 02:02.960
But actually salvation is from God alone.

02:03.020 --> 02:07.848
It's a gift from God alone through Jesus' death and resurrection.

02:07.888 --> 02:18.066
And the context he's speaking to is a church that has been built from people with a background of the Jewish faith and also from

02:18.370 --> 02:19.371
no faith at all.

02:19.932 --> 02:26.441
So he's also trying to unify that church together and saying that salvation is available to all.

02:27.983 --> 02:39.558
So Romans 10 verse nine says this, if you declare with your mouth, Jesus is Lord, and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved.

02:41.381 --> 02:44.185
So I'm gonna unpack what this means and break it down.

02:44.245 --> 02:48.210
But before I go on, when I was given this verse,

02:48.322 --> 02:49.864
I've got a bit stuck.

02:49.884 --> 03:06.789
I was like, oh, I'm not sure what I think about this by itself, because it is tempting for us to hear this and be like, well, I need to go and share the gospel and tell people about Jesus in order to be saved.

03:06.849 --> 03:13.138
There's a temptation for us to make it about what we need to do in order to be saved.

03:14.690 --> 03:30.260
But I want us to remind ourselves of what Jesus tells us here, that God for God so loved the world that he gave his one and only son, that whoever believes in him shall not perish but have eternal life.

03:31.462 --> 03:37.874
So I believe firmly that Jesus Christ is a central point to our salvation.

03:38.690 --> 03:41.354
We don't have to work it out in order to receive it.

03:41.394 --> 03:49.847
It's a free gift, but Paul is commenting on the fact that we have this inward belief and maybe there's something needs to happen externally as well.

03:51.890 --> 03:54.894
So let's unpack the context.

03:54.994 --> 03:59.221
Why would Paul then be saying you need to confess your faith?

03:59.241 --> 04:02.085
What is the context, the audience that he's talking to?

04:04.288 --> 04:05.490
So firstly,

04:06.210 --> 04:09.493
as I've already touched on, he is speaking to the Jewish nation.

04:11.175 --> 04:27.932
And this phrase, Jesus is Lord, declare with your mouth, Jesus is Lord, would have struck a chord particularly with the Jewish people because they themselves had and have similar phrasing.

04:28.933 --> 04:34.098
They have something called the Shema, which is a declaration

04:34.338 --> 04:42.909
of their faith, which says this in Deuteronomy 6, 4, here O Israel, the Lord our God, the Lord is one.

04:45.553 --> 04:55.446
So this statement of faith, this or creed is what we, another word for it, was something that the Jews declared to say that they were different.

04:55.827 --> 04:57.188
We believe in one God.

04:57.409 --> 04:59.792
We don't have many gods like you other nations.

04:59.872 --> 05:04.338
We believe in one God who went with them wherever they traveled.

05:04.898 --> 05:07.241
This was a core belief statement for the Jews.

05:08.242 --> 05:25.425
So poor being aware of this and aware of the parameters of Judaism, I think when he's declaring, you need to declare that Jesus is Lord, what he's doing is he's identifying the Old Testament Lord with Jesus.

05:27.328 --> 05:34.898
He's emphasizing that Jesus is a fulfillment of the Jewish faith, a continuation and not something new.

05:34.978 --> 05:36.199
that should be avoided.

05:37.801 --> 05:40.383
Okay, secondly, he's speaking to the culture.

05:42.305 --> 05:44.107
So there's a whole other context.

05:44.167 --> 05:44.887
We're in Rome.

05:45.088 --> 05:46.429
Romans are in charge.

05:46.489 --> 05:51.834
We have a Caesar who is in charge, and he's getting quite big for his boots.

05:51.914 --> 05:54.657
He also thinks that he is God.

05:54.837 --> 05:58.621
He is becoming divine, and he should be worshipped as such.

05:59.962 --> 06:04.306
And so there is this thing of, well, you need to declare that Caesar is Lord.

06:05.026 --> 06:07.630
And if you don't, then you could be killed.

06:08.551 --> 06:12.496
And so I think Paul is saying, you know, well, that's not okay.

06:12.516 --> 06:14.599
We're not going to be declaring that Caesar is Lord.

06:15.120 --> 06:23.592
I was reminded of Mark 12, 17, when Jesus talks about this, it give back to Caesar, what is Caesar?

06:23.612 --> 06:26.916
This is talking about taxes and to God, what is God's?

06:27.557 --> 06:28.779
And they were amazed at him.

06:29.820 --> 06:33.906
So Jesus was talking about, you know, we practically were part of this system.

06:34.018 --> 06:38.524
We share our taxes, but our spiritual allegiance is to God.

06:38.544 --> 06:42.749
And so Paul is saying, we need to stand against the culture.

06:42.769 --> 06:44.972
We need to make a political statement here.

06:47.615 --> 06:54.223
Thirdly, to protect and build on the Christian tradition.

06:55.565 --> 07:02.674
So Paul not only is sharing the gospel, but he's also part of the early church

07:03.554 --> 07:11.026
who was forming the foundations of a tradition that would get passed down for generations to come.

07:12.689 --> 07:23.526
So this creed, Jesus is Lord, which is probably the shortest creed of the New Testament, is a core statement of what Christians believe.

07:25.389 --> 07:30.257
And knowing what we believe, knowing our boundaries and our beliefs are really important, aren't they?

07:30.277 --> 07:31.218
We need them.

07:31.650 --> 07:33.832
We need to know our core beliefs.

07:34.473 --> 07:35.875
Our church has them.

07:35.935 --> 07:37.717
We have values on our website.

07:37.737 --> 07:38.838
This is what we believe.

07:38.858 --> 07:44.244
And it was important as they were laying these foundations to get that right.

07:44.284 --> 07:47.528
We don't want to have any impurity being passed down.

07:47.588 --> 07:50.411
We need to know what it is that we believe.

07:51.252 --> 07:56.578
And they make up our identity and have stood the test of time.

07:58.861 --> 07:59.922
And then lastly,

08:01.282 --> 08:02.944
This could be for them and for us.

08:04.967 --> 08:08.953
Confessing that Jesus' Lord also speaks to ourselves.

08:11.036 --> 08:18.668
Galatians 2.20, Paul says, I have been crucified with Christ, and I no longer live, but Christ lives in me.

08:18.708 --> 08:27.060
The life I now live in the body, I live by faith in the Son of God, who loved me and gave himself for me.

08:27.100 --> 08:31.186
So when we declare,

08:32.066 --> 08:34.149
that Jesus is Lord.

08:34.790 --> 08:39.035
We are tying our allegiance, we are pledging our allegiance to Jesus.

08:40.858 --> 08:44.282
If Jesus is Lord, then what we're saying is, well, I'm not.

08:44.342 --> 08:51.752
I am giving my servitude, my obedience and surrendering my life to Him.

08:52.373 --> 08:57.260
And from experience, that is something that happens, has to happen a lot.

08:57.640 --> 09:02.066
Maybe even daily, we need to remind ourselves, Jesus, you are Lord.

09:02.530 --> 09:03.571
and I am not.

09:06.034 --> 09:15.425
Okay, let's move on in this verse onto, and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead.

09:16.547 --> 09:21.433
So the second half of that segment there forms another creed.

09:21.513 --> 09:23.055
It's another statement of belief.

09:23.575 --> 09:25.938
God raised him from the dead.

09:26.018 --> 09:29.062
In order to be a Christian, you need to understand this truth.

09:29.122 --> 09:31.565
If you don't believe this, then you're not a Christian, you know?

09:32.246 --> 09:35.971
So this was really important to get this drill down.

09:36.011 --> 09:39.215
It validates everything.

09:39.235 --> 09:44.362
Resurrection validates the claims that Jesus made when he was alive.

09:44.402 --> 09:49.829
Him rising from the dead confirms his claim that he is God.

09:50.770 --> 09:53.874
He is God's son and has power over death.

09:54.562 --> 09:57.285
And again, it fulfills that Old Testament prophecy.

09:57.625 --> 09:59.528
This isn't new, this is a continuation.

09:59.588 --> 10:04.493
And then believe in your heart.

10:05.955 --> 10:08.458
So this I think is harder to grasp, isn't it?

10:09.279 --> 10:13.143
Harder to kind of get language around, believing in your heart.

10:14.384 --> 10:19.971
But I think what Paul is trying to say, that this is more than just something that you know to be true.

10:19.991 --> 10:22.834
It's something more than knowledge.

10:23.618 --> 10:32.074
It is knowledge that has consumed every single part of your being to produce that outward transformation.

10:33.076 --> 10:38.767
So inward belief that has to produce a change in who we are.

10:41.012 --> 10:46.482
So for the Jewish nation, you know, their identity was tied up in who they were and what they did.

10:48.706 --> 10:54.011
But God is looking for, as Paul says in Romans 2, at circumcision of the heart.

10:55.953 --> 11:04.221
And I think we see it a few times in Scripture when people know who Jesus is, they know that he's important, but they don't quite get it.

11:05.082 --> 11:11.288
And I was reading the story of Martha and Mary, and that is preached on a lot, isn't it?

11:11.409 --> 11:13.170
And lots of things are drawn out of that.

11:14.772 --> 11:16.914
But I just wonder if

11:17.154 --> 11:20.858
Martha just didn't quite get who was in her house that day.

11:22.279 --> 11:24.141
Mary understood who he was.

11:24.441 --> 11:28.786
Mary understood that she needed to be sat at his feet, listening and learning.

11:30.448 --> 11:39.257
But Martha hadn't realized that actually, although hospitality is important and especially in that culture, it was more important to be with Jesus.

11:39.357 --> 11:40.738
This was a special moment.

11:41.439 --> 11:44.402
She hadn't quite received that depth of revelation.

11:47.138 --> 11:53.347
So belief in your heart, causing us for it to change something outwardly.

11:56.851 --> 11:59.836
The last bit of that verse, and you will be saved.

12:01.578 --> 12:13.234
Paul is clear, there is no ifs or buts, so if you do this or if you do that, he's given us a confident assurance, and Richard will talk about that more next week.

12:15.490 --> 12:28.224
We don't confess to achieve salvation, but that confession comes from an overflow of a belief in who Jesus is and what he has done for us and humanity.

12:29.245 --> 12:31.448
It is an evidence of our belief.

12:32.629 --> 12:37.775
So confession is part of our growth and it strengthens our faith in him.

12:39.837 --> 12:41.799
So what does this mean for us?

12:41.859 --> 12:44.402
What is he saying to us then this morning?

12:45.986 --> 12:52.757
So I believe firstly, Paul is saying that God is not looking for anonymous Christians.

12:55.281 --> 13:04.997
He is looking for Christians who are willing to share their faith, to let people know that Jesus has transformed their lives.

13:05.918 --> 13:10.405
And I think firstly, the way that we can can confess is through baptism.

13:12.148 --> 13:13.330
So if you're a

13:13.570 --> 13:24.367
You know, if you believe that Jesus has died for you, but you haven't yet been baptized, I really encourage you to do that because it is a great moment of confession, of declaration in a public space.

13:25.809 --> 13:28.433
And do come and talk to me if that's something you'd like to do.

13:28.473 --> 13:30.536
And we'd love to walk that with you.

13:34.081 --> 13:36.826
But yeah, so do people know that you're a Christian?

13:36.866 --> 13:39.890
Do your friends, your work colleagues?

13:41.012 --> 13:41.312
Why?

13:41.352 --> 13:42.354
Why not?

13:42.594 --> 13:44.736
That's a question for me as well, you know?

13:44.756 --> 13:55.386
I love the book of James and it's quite... What's the word?

13:56.708 --> 13:57.408
Hardline.

13:58.449 --> 13:59.590
Yeah, hardline, I think.

14:00.591 --> 14:05.276
And it talks about faith by itself if it's not accompanied by action.

14:06.637 --> 14:07.158
It's dead.

14:07.198 --> 14:11.762
And James uses the example of Abraham that he was made righteous.

14:14.050 --> 14:17.795
and one with God because his action demonstrated a trust in him.

14:19.517 --> 14:21.639
So our faith is an active living faith.

14:22.720 --> 14:31.151
If our actions are showing that actually we rely more on ourselves than God, then what is that saying about our faith?

14:31.691 --> 14:35.856
Secondly, God is looking at our hearts.

14:37.478 --> 14:43.826
So has our belief and our understanding moved from that place of, I get that that's true and that

14:43.938 --> 14:47.422
I'm saved to that sincere reliance on God.

14:48.324 --> 14:49.785
Do we stake our lives on it?

14:50.306 --> 14:52.048
Do we make life decisions on it?

14:53.250 --> 14:55.593
Or do we tack our faith onto our weak?

14:58.677 --> 15:01.000
Are we still the Lord of our own lives?

15:01.100 --> 15:06.006
And I think, you know, if we're here this morning and I think we probably have to do it every day.

15:06.066 --> 15:11.453
And we think, actually, yeah, Jesus, I'm not sure that you are Lord.

15:11.513 --> 15:12.434
And I think that I've

15:12.642 --> 15:20.076
like to be in control a lot of the time, then repentance is required, you know, and I think that's just what we do.

15:20.156 --> 15:22.921
It's a constant coming to the Lord, isn't it?

15:27.529 --> 15:30.896
Thirdly, the gospel needs to be shared.

15:30.936 --> 15:34.322
So we

15:34.882 --> 15:40.049
aren't in a society I don't think quite like what Paul was talking to.

15:40.109 --> 15:46.097
We're not having to declare that someone else is Lord or pledge our allegiance to other people.

15:46.157 --> 15:54.068
But our society still has creed, still has beliefs and still need Jesus.

15:55.750 --> 16:04.242
You know, perhaps they think, well, let's drink and eat for tomorrow we die or you do you or all paths lead to God.

16:04.322 --> 16:08.767
We hold the truth inside of us, all these things that aren't true.

16:08.787 --> 16:14.574
And Paul says that a few verses are in Romans 10, 14 to 15.

16:16.056 --> 16:18.920
How then can they call on the one they have not believed?

16:19.761 --> 16:23.525
And how can they believe in the one of whom they have not heard?

16:23.545 --> 16:27.150
And how can they hear without someone preaching to them?

16:27.170 --> 16:30.834
And how can anyone preach unless they are sent?

16:31.970 --> 16:37.657
As it is written, how beautiful are the feet of those who bring good news?

16:43.804 --> 16:47.708
We have within us good news.

16:48.089 --> 16:52.234
We have a gift that has been given us to us freely.

16:52.254 --> 16:57.199
And there are people who don't yet know that.

16:57.640 --> 16:59.442
There are people who are dying.

17:01.090 --> 17:02.912
Believe in me and you will not perish.

17:05.275 --> 17:07.557
Are we convicted by that truth?

17:07.657 --> 17:12.683
Or do we take compassion like Jesus when we're interacting with other people?

17:12.723 --> 17:16.947
Or maybe we think, well, that was Paul's job.

17:17.228 --> 17:18.769
You know, that was his anointing.

17:18.829 --> 17:26.278
He had a particular anointing and it can be tempting to think, well, that's not my role, my gifting.

17:26.698 --> 17:30.322
I know for myself, the idea of sharing the gospel does not

17:30.402 --> 17:34.869
come easily is not something that comes naturally.

17:34.889 --> 17:37.834
It has to be like an intentional choice.

17:37.974 --> 17:45.386
However, I'm reminded of what Jesus said before he went back to heaven in Matthew 28.

17:45.546 --> 17:56.703
Go and make disciples of all nations baptizing them in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit and teaching them to obey everything I have commanded you.

17:56.743 --> 17:58.386
And surely,

17:58.626 --> 18:02.091
I am with you always to the very end of the age.

18:03.473 --> 18:07.118
I don't believe Jesus was just talking to his 11 disciples.

18:07.979 --> 18:14.447
You know, he was talking to all of us that each and every one of us carry this light.

18:16.450 --> 18:22.759
And as we go out, we have the amazing opportunity to share this truth, this light with other people.

18:22.799 --> 18:28.146
And I just have this picture as we go out into our own walks of life.

18:28.514 --> 18:32.419
bearing this light and just sharing that truth with Jesus.

18:32.519 --> 18:38.347
You know, the wonderful thing is this could feel like a burden, but the promise is that he is with us.

18:38.527 --> 18:46.698
God, the living God is with us and conviction and that revelation can only come through him.

18:47.098 --> 18:55.890
We can partner with him, we can share that news, but whether that person responds in belief is not up to us.

18:56.258 --> 18:58.662
And that just releases so much pressure, doesn't it?

19:01.826 --> 19:08.677
But yeah, as we go out with our lights, we just have this picture of us with the people around us and other lights turning on.

19:10.600 --> 19:13.524
And then they go in and other light turns on.

19:14.145 --> 19:16.308
And that's the beauty, isn't it, of the gospel?

19:16.348 --> 19:20.014
And that, you know, I just, that excites me.

19:21.035 --> 19:22.738
Because when you see people,

19:24.418 --> 19:30.444
Suddenly that realization that, oh, this is more than just something I've heard.

19:30.485 --> 19:32.106
This is life-changing.

19:32.126 --> 19:34.008
This is transformation.

19:34.068 --> 19:38.033
And I realized that God loves me and that he wants to be in relationship with me.

19:38.053 --> 19:39.054
And he created me.

19:39.714 --> 19:46.722
When you see that penny drop in someone's face, you're like, wow, there is nothing better than this is there.

19:48.003 --> 19:54.290
And we get to be part of that as his church, as his good news, as his hands and feet,

19:54.594 --> 19:55.736
How amazing is that?

20:02.285 --> 20:15.403
At the end of last year, Lucas shared with us that he felt that the law was saying to us that the last five years has been a time when life church has been a landing pad.

20:16.464 --> 20:20.650
Lots of different people landing and worrying for different reasons.

20:21.671 --> 20:23.634
We now need to be a launch pad.

20:24.034 --> 20:29.563
a place that people launch from into mission and to serve our community.

20:35.873 --> 20:40.140
So I just want to reiterate that sharing the gospel is an evidence.

20:40.781 --> 20:43.124
It's an overflow of our relationship with him.

20:44.086 --> 20:45.809
It's not a means to us, our salvation.

20:47.451 --> 20:51.698
But what is it that's maybe stopping me, stopping you from doing that?

20:52.194 --> 20:54.037
Perhaps it's the lack of knowing how.

20:56.320 --> 20:57.121
Just practice.

20:57.181 --> 21:05.993
Maybe we're scared of what people will think of us or being condemned by certain people.

21:07.135 --> 21:08.376
But I don't know.

21:08.396 --> 21:14.405
I'm just feeling like if we all felt we were doing this together, we'd be encouraged.

21:14.445 --> 21:21.234
And if we started hearing those testimonies come in of, well, I shared the gospel or I told someone a Christian

21:21.506 --> 21:25.471
that actually were really open to it, how encouraging would that be?

21:27.734 --> 21:34.063
But I think that practice is really helpful in learning as well, just to get over that bump.

21:34.924 --> 21:46.580
And there are a few things coming up that I'd love to invite you to, just to help and equip us in learning how to and to be more open in this.

21:47.441 --> 21:51.346
And yeah, so March the 29th,

21:51.490 --> 21:58.239
we are being, yeah, we have got Simon Gilbow coming to talk to us.

21:58.360 --> 22:05.089
He's gonna be here the whole weekend, sharing at different events over Life Church, but he is a missionary.

22:05.189 --> 22:17.266
He worked in Burundi for many years, and he still supports them with a charity in helping alleviate poverty, but also sharing.

22:17.634 --> 22:18.235
the gospel.

22:18.455 --> 22:19.376
But he's going to be with us.

22:19.436 --> 22:22.199
He's going to preach here on the 29th of March.

22:24.041 --> 22:33.110
But I kind of wanted to use his breadth of knowledge and experience to extend that time.

22:33.290 --> 22:38.535
So we're going to ask him to participate in the question and answer lunch.

22:39.076 --> 22:42.399
So after church on the 29th, we're going to go over to Bethel.

22:43.100 --> 22:45.202
We'll have lunch together and then we'll

22:45.538 --> 22:46.479
The floor will be open.

22:46.540 --> 22:48.503
We can ask him different questions.

22:49.284 --> 22:53.470
He is a really inspiring chap and I think will be really encouraged.

22:54.111 --> 22:59.740
We're also looking at getting childcare as well because we want as many people to be able to come as possible.

23:01.142 --> 23:02.524
So do you put that in your diaries?

23:02.644 --> 23:07.913
And what I'll do is I'll send out an invitation as well so I can get numbers for food.

23:09.575 --> 23:14.002
And as we heard in the notice video, we have got alpha coming up.

23:15.170 --> 23:23.280
And this is a really good way, you know, if we're not confident in sharing the gospel or in having deep conversations about our faith.

23:23.701 --> 23:29.969
It's a great way of bringing people along in spaces that do create conversation and go deeper.

23:31.290 --> 23:36.236
So on the 9th of March, there is an explore and equip where you can just find out more.

23:36.397 --> 23:39.921
Is there something you would like to bring your friends or family along to?

23:39.941 --> 23:43.986
And then the actual course starts on the 13th of April.

23:44.386 --> 23:47.631
at Bethel and there will be flyers on the front desk.

23:47.812 --> 23:50.997
So please do take take some and start thinking and praying.

23:51.017 --> 23:54.823
Like, is there anyone that God is just revealing to me is, you know what?

23:55.344 --> 23:58.449
Yeah, I think they'd really be open to that.

23:59.951 --> 24:00.913
Yeah, it'd be really good.

24:00.953 --> 24:11.410
So I'm just going to read that verse over us again.

24:15.650 --> 24:23.562
If you declare with your mouth, Jesus is Lord and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved.

24:25.245 --> 24:26.267
